Do you want to play this fun word game with me? After you watch the video, come up with your own word and put it in the comments! It’s addicting!

This word building activity will engage all your students while teaching prefixes, suffixes, spelling patterns, and new vocabulary! You can use this as a center or partner work, enrichment homework, whole or small group instruction, or even a five minute filler! Digital version with Google Slides and answer keys included.

node.text:
New space, new theme boards! I can’t wait to fill these up with all the books we share together! 

My theme boards are one of my most referenced spaces in our classroom! It’s amazing how quickly students catch on to theme and love discussing theme because of this visual! 

Here’s how it works:
We discuss theme for EVERY book we share together. The books may not end up on the same theme board each year because it depends on how convincing my students are with their evidence. After the possible themes are presented, our class votes on which one they felt was the strongest even though all the choices may be good, the one with the most votes wins.

•I don’t have a list of theme books because this resource can be used with any fictional text and many books have several possible themes. The students decide which theme is the strongest.

•Our theme boards only include books we share as a class, this way they can all provide evidence to support or refute a theme. 

This resource now includes a DIGITAL version. 🙌

Link to resource in my profile: bit.ly/themeboards #booklover #book #readingteacher #booktheme

Want to empower your students through peer recognition? These individual desk awards have such a positive impact while students celebrate each other by acknowledging and recognizing their everyday wins and successes!

This is an INSTANT community builder! You pick the behaviors you want to see in your class and let your students find peer examples! 🙌

We take a couple minutes at the end of the day to celebrate a few students! ❤️

If your students are sitting in groups this year, I also have group awards! This gives them such ownership and pride of the roles they want to take and see in their classroom.

Let them do the work!!! These Table Talk discussion cards CHANGED so much of the conversations had in our classroom which empowered my students. TUNE TUESDAY is definitely a FAVORITE in our class! The conversations/annotations at the end of year compared to the beginning of the year is just mind-blowing! They’re not just surface level thinkers anymore and the way they challenge each other’s thinking is incredible! 

*Swipe to see it in action! 🙌

Close reading with music engages all my learners! They look forward to reading the text multiple times and finding evidence to prove their thinking!

During Tune Tuesday (can be done any day of the week! 😝) we:

•close read
•annotate the text
•determine the theme 
•appreciate author’s craft 
•learn new vocabulary
•find figurative language
•author’s point of view 
•tone/mood
•cite evidence 
•use accountable talk 
•debate with our classmates
•and of course, sing along! 

If you want to try something new next year, you have to try Tune Tuesday with your class!

There’s a digital version using Google Slides to all the sets!
